Issues found and resolved during acceptance
- A global unique policy_hash incorrectly prevented two Jobs from sharing one policy. Migration
  0014 replaces it with the intended per-Job hash scope.
- The strict AI DTO initially received internal policy/contract fields. The assembler now strips
  them before strict parsing.
- The retained Queue Worker accepted only Interest V1. It now accepts pinned V2 Interests without
  weakening historical compatibility.
- Demo reset could observe an IDLE worker while another lease was active. It now polls boundedly for
  the resulting projection.
- Old migration and documentation tests stopped at migration 0012 and encoded complete-market Feed
  access. Their assertions now test 0013/0014 and the new fail-closed access semantics.
- Port 3000 was occupied by the visible development app. Playwright now supports an isolated port;
  local MinIO permits the explicit 3100 test origin.

Skipped and blocked
- Two existing conditional integration assertions were skipped by their own environment guards.
- No required Eligibility verification was blocked.

Known boundary
- SYNTHETIC_SOURCE_ATTACHED is not ownership, employment, credential, or capability verification.
- RECORDED_LIVE is Demo-only and pin-validated. Runtime LIVE failures never read it or another fixed
  fixture.
- GPT controls Candidate-side access only; it cannot rank the Queue, expose a Candidate list to the
  Recruiter, allocate Attention, or perform Human Review.
